com.axibase.tsd.service.el.series.context

Class SeriesContext

  • java.lang.Object
    • ParserContext
      • com.axibase.tsd.service.el.series.context.DateTimeContext
        • com.axibase.tsd.service.el.series.context.SeriesContext

  • public class SeriesContext
extends DateTimeContext
    Context of single series. The following variables are available in the context:
    • Series series - series for which expression is evaluated.
    • int tIndex - Total index - 0-based index of current sample in series, if expression is evaluated for each sample, or index of the first sample in current interval if expression evaluated for each interval.
    • long t - current timestamp. It has correct value if expression is evaluated for each sample.
    • double v - current value. It has correct value if expression is evaluated for each sample.
    • int iIndex - Interval index - 0-based index of current interval, if expression is evaluated for each interval in turn.
    • int sIndex - Sample index - 0-based index of current sample among all samples in current interval. (If expression is evaluated for each interval and for each sample in interval.)
    • long intervalStart - start time of current interval. Has meaning if expression is evaluated for some interval.
    • long intervalEnd - end time of current interval. Has meaning if expression is evaluated for some interval.
    • NavigableMap<Long, Double> intervalSamples - all samples within current time interval.
    • Map<String, Number> memory - this context storage. Use it to share values between several evaluations in this context. For example, when expression is evaluated for each series timestamp, the single evaluation context is used, and its memory is available at each evaluation.

      • ds

        public DescriptiveStatistics ds()
        Return the DescriptiveStatistics instance, filled by not NaN values. In case of calculations per interval - Series.calculate(String, String, String...), and Series.forEach(String, String, String...) statistics contains values within current time interval. In case of single evaluation - Series.calculate(String) statistics contains all series values. In case of Series.forEach(String) statistics is empty.
